    {
      "id": "cee8e2bd-aa51-42b7-8cbd-990dfcf04f7d",
      "name": "Multi-Calendar Setup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -820,
        -420
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Multi-calendar setup \u2014 4 accounts\n\nPolls the primary calendar of all 4 accounts: eganbonde@gmail.com (Personal), egachuu@gmail.com (Tech), egan@norrai.co (Norr AI), hello@norrai.co (Norr AI). Unlike the Gmail collector, there's no per-item loop here \u2014 one `getAll` fetch per calendar, so only `Get Events` + `Build Event Batch` are duplicated per account; everything from `Merge Calendar Batches` onward (classify, parse, split, upsert) is a single shared execution per run.\n\nSet each `Get Events \u2014 {email}` node's credential to the matching account before import (placeholders: GCAL_CREDENTIAL_EGANBONDE / _EGACHUU / _EGAN_NORRAI / _HELLO_NORRAI).\n\n**event_id namespacing:** each event's `event_id` sent to Claude (and later used as `source_ref`) is qualified as `{calendar_email}:{google_event_id}` in `Build Event Batch`, not the bare Google event id \u2014 `UNIQUE(source, source_ref)` is shared across all 4 calendars under source='calendar'. The classifier prompt is unmodified (LOCKED); it just echoes back whatever `event_id` string it was given.\n\n**Same alias caveat as the Gmail collector:** if egan@norrai.co and hello@norrai.co are the same Workspace mailbox/calendar via a send-as alias, this polls one calendar twice \u2014 verify before enabling.",
        "height": 460,
        "width": 520
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "92db51d8-aa9f-46df-8d2f-beb07d8306a8",
      "name": "Merge Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -400,
        -220
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Merge Calendar Batches\n\n`numberInputs: 4`, one per calendar branch's `Build Event Batch \u2014 X` output \u2014 waits for all 4 before `Combine Event Batches` flattens them into one `events` array. **Verify after import** that the node renders 4 input handles.",
        "height": 180,
        "width": 340
      }
    }
  ],
